				25 = error: gain below low limit
				26 = error: gain above high limit
				27 = warning: gain near low limit
				28 = warning: gain near high limit
				
				All table statuses are set to 1, when device boots up.
				
				All table statuses which are not run at this time, are set to 1.
				
				All table statuses are set to 2, when one (or all) is started.
				
				If one option ends to error, then all the rest (bigger indexes) are set to 17 and 
				transponderSetButtonLastRunErrorIndex is set to this index and transponderSetButtonLastRunStatus is set to 19.
				So the first error index is visible.
				
				If one (or more) option ends to warning, then all the rest are run similar as the option ends with 3 and 
				transponderSetButtonLastRunErrorIndex is set to this index and transponderSetButtonLastRunStatus is set to 18.
