		-- 1.3.6.1.4.1.3715.100.94.5
		automaticAlignmentRunNowSelected OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX INTEGER
			ACCESS read-write
			STATUS mandatory
			DESCRIPTION
				"Run now selected options (bitmask; multiple bits are allowed).
				
				Index for option in automaticAlignmentOptionsTable is in format 2^(bit+1).
				E.g. automaticAlignmentOptionIndex.8 means that 8=2^3, where (bit+1) is 3, so bit = 2.
				
				Bit 0: 0x0001
				Bit 1: 0x0002
				Bit 2: 0x0004
				Bit 3: 0x0008
				Bit 4: 0x0010
				Bit 5: 0x0020
				Bit 6: 0x0040
				Bit 7: 0x0080
				Bit 8: 0x0100
				Bit 9: 0x0200
				Bit 10: 0x0400
				Bit 11: 0x0800
				etc.
				
				Note that some options may override others.
				
				Read: Options bitmask run last time. If no options run, returns 0.
				Write: Bitmask for options to be run immediately. Note! Options are not stored to non-volatile memory and selections on automaticAlignemntOptionsTable (automaticAlignmentOptionEnable) are not affected."
			::= { automaticAlignment 5 }

		
	
